    },
    {
      "id": "quote:2941638dec44fe73",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 163,
        "char_start": 13,
        "episode_id": "22aa61d4-d535-5e72-ae9b-d44d9a3054d1",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Welcome to The Long View. Today we're exploring the biohacking premise in depth with Dr. Elena Fischer, researcher in metabolic and longevity science.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 6000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 0,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-02",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Dr. Elena Fischer"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:d0b7599bb09cd3f0",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 242,
        "char_start": 183,
        "episode_id": "22aa61d4-d535-5e72-ae9b-d44d9a3054d1",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Thanks, Alex Morgan. This is a topic I've spent decades on.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 12000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 6000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:baba871d00abab8a",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 457,
        "char_start": 256,
        "episode_id": "22aa61d4-d535-5e72-ae9b-d44d9a3054d1",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "This episode is brought to you by Linear. Linear is the issue tracker built for speed — keyboard-first, fast search, and a clean roadmap view your team actually uses. Get started at linear.com/podcast.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:f3fd455d4a6f577d",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 519,
        "char_start": 457,
        "episode_id": "22aa61d4-d535-5e72-ae9b-d44d9a3054d1",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Why is systems thinking the part that most analyses get wrong?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:3f376f4c80f9ccc5",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 775,
        "char_start": 539,
        "episode_id": "22aa61d4-d535-5e72-ae9b-d44d9a3054d1",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "The short answer is Biohacking is mostly hygiene factors and recovery — the exotic stuff is downstream. Teams working with WHOOP run into this constantly. The framing matters because it tells you which trade-offs you're actually making.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:60c1af9601e83355",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 843,
        "char_start": 789,
        "episode_id": "22aa61d4-d535-5e72-ae9b-d44d9a3054d1",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Is there a counterexample that would change your view?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
